===Etymology===
Old English ''ago'', ''[[agon]]'', [[past participle]] of ''agon'', to go away, to pass by, Anglo-Saxon ''[[agan]]'', to pass away.

===Pronunciation===
*ə-gō', /əˈɡəʊ/, /<tt>@'g@U</tt>/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊ|-əʊ]]

===Adverb===
'''ago'''

# Past; gone by; since.
#:''ten years ago''
#:''gone long ago''
# {{obsolete}} nearly gone; [[dead]] (used in [[w:Devonshire|Devonshire]] at the turn of the [[w:19th century|19th century]])''

